6.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Eudes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of Croatian and Slovenian <b>Rudež</b>: nickname derived from <i>rud</i> ‘red, reddish’, or, alternatively, from <i>rud</i> ‘curly’ (standard Slovenian <i>rod</i>; compare   Rodes  ). In Croatia, the surname is also found in the form <b>Rudeš</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodes","meanings":["Catalan (<b>Rodés</b>): habitational name from any of several places called Rodés, mainly those in El Pallars and El Conflent districts, in northern Catalonia.","Catalan: variant of   Roda  , from Catalan <i>rodes</i>, plural of <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’.","English: variant of   Rhodes  . Compare   Rhode  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guy Eudes de Dampierre was born in 1010, in Dampierre, Aube, Grand Est, France, his father, Hildouin de Dampierre, was 29 and his mother, Melisende de Limoges, was 20. He died in 1072, in his hometown, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1010–1072":"1010–1072","1015–1076":"1015–1076","1012–Female":"1012–Surnud","1040–1095":"1040–1095","0981–1050":"0981–1050","0990–1010":"0990–1010","0981":"0981","1015":"1015","0990":"0990","1012":"1012","1010":"1010","1076":"1076","1040":"1040","1095":"1095","1072":"1072","1050":"1050","ABT 1050":"umbes 1050","Mortagne, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Mortagne-au-Perche, Orne, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Dampierre,